@startuml recall-internal-delete
' SEQUENCE: the Recall DELETE path in isolation
' (services.source_registry.main -> adapters.state.state.recall_delete_vector).
' Delete = UPSERT a TOMBSTONE (deleted=true) stamped with a FRESH lsn from
' recall_lsn_seq (the SAME atomic upsert-increment the write uses), so the
' tombstone is strictly ABOVE the watermark -- NEVER an in-place flip of an old
' row's lsn. Last-write-wins on the PK. Committed before returning ->
' synchronous read-your-deletes. The cap/CONSOLIDATE enqueue lives in
' recall-internal-bounding, not here.

title Recall internals: delete = above-watermark tombstone (read-your-deletes)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "client" as client
participant "cp\n(recall_delete_vector)" as cp
database "recall_lsn_seq" as seq
database "recall_vectors" as rv

client -> cp : DELETE /vectors/{id}
activate cp

== one transaction on a dedicated recall connection ==

cp -> seq : INSERT .. ON CONFLICT\nDO UPDATE last_lsn = last_lsn + 1\nRETURNING last_lsn
activate seq
seq --> cp : fresh lsn  (= max(lsn)+1)
deactivate seq
note right of seq #FDF3E7
  A FRESH lsn, strictly above max(lsn) and thus
  above ANY watermark. We do NOT flip deleted in
  place / reuse the old lsn: a tombstone at-or-
  below the watermark is excluded from the union
  (the id never deletes) AND is trim-eligible
  before its delete is folded (the id resurrects).
end note

cp -> rv : UPSERT (id, deleted=TRUE, lsn=fresh,\nzero-vector placeholder of dataset dim)\nON CONFLICT DO UPDATE lsn=EXCLUDED, deleted=TRUE
activate rv
note right of rv #E9F7E9
  Last-write-wins on (tenant,dataset,id): an
  existing live/deleted row is overwritten with
  deleted=true + the fresh higher lsn. A consolidated-only
  delete (no prior recall row) gets a dimension-
  matched zero placeholder for the NOT NULL column
  (never ranked -- the search excludes tombstones).
end note
rv --> cp : tombstone written
deactivate rv

cp -> cp : COMMIT
note over cp #E7F3FD
  Synchronous read-your-deletes: the tombstone is
  durable BEFORE returning, so an immediate query
  suppresses the id at once. RB_RECALL on -> 204.
end note
cp --> client : 204 No Content
deactivate cp

@enduml
